[metadata]
Name:Hokori, Dust Drinker — each player untaps exactly one land
Goal:Survive
Turns:4
Difficulty:Easy
Description:Hokori, Dust Drinker: "Lands don't untap during their controllers' untap steps. At the beginning of each player's upkeep, that player untaps a land they control." The untap-step replacement stops ALL lands from untapping normally; the upkeep trigger gives each player back exactly one. P0 controls Hokori and 3 tapped Plains; P1 controls 2 tapped Forests. The puzzle starts at P0's upkeep (turn 2): the trigger fires for P0 (ActivePlayer = P0) and untaps exactly one land (UntapOne). On the next turn P1's upkeep fires and untaps exactly one of P1's lands. After both triggers fire, P0 still has 2 tapped Plains (not all 3 untapped), and P1 still has 1 tapped Forest.

